{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StringType","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The emphasis of ","type":"text"},{"code":"GString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is on text, typically UTF-8. Crucially, the “str” member","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GString"},{"text":" is guaranteed to have a trailing nul character, and it is therefore","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always safe to call functions such as "},{"code":"strchr()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strdup()"},{"text":" on it.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GString"},{"text":" can also hold arbitrary binary data, because it has a “len” member,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which includes any possible embedded nul characters in the data. Conceptually then,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is like a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GByteArray"},{"type":"text","text":" with the addition of many convenience methods for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"text, and a guaranteed nul terminator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringType","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GString","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type t